Some Nigerian have taken to social media platforms to react to the decision of the federal government to lift the ban on Twitter’s operations in Nigeria. The announcement on the lifting of the ban comes 222 days after the suspension of Twitter’s operation in Nigeria. Taking the decision to suspend Twitter’s operations at time — on June 5 — the federal government had said the microblogging platform was allowing content that “undermine” Nigeria’s corporate existence. However, following the reversal of the ban on Wednesday, there were mixed reactions on social media. Below are some reactions on Twitter. Great News for Nigeria People and Busineses,Buhari regime backs down on Twitter ban after 222 days. — Chris Kirwa (@chriskirwa) January 12, 2022  I thought Buhari will lift twitter ban if Nigeria promise him third term APC don loose guard — sun (@iamnelsun) January 12, 2022  Welcome back to @Twitter Nigeria! — Femi Fani-Kayode (@realFFK) January 12, 2022  My people stay calm, no vex buhari before midnight. — Fatima Khan (Mrs) (@RubbyQueen__) January 12, 2022  Here wondering what Buhari first post will be like. CMs will be chaotic — Lay Low (@Thinnygram2) January 12, 2022  Buhari will be dealt with on twitter tomorrow, the DSS should be prepared for massive arrest and intimidation — Temitope Adedigba (@tooshtpain1) January 12, 2022  Buhari was impressed by the Super Eagles performance yesterday and decided to lift the ban on Twitter.. — Ghost (@Awwal_Gimba) January 12, 2022  Twitter ban that Buhari was supposed to lift on the eve of the 2023 presidential election. This APC no even get liver — 'Fisayo Soyombo (@fisayosoyombo) January 12, 2022  I'm really pained that Buhari had that much power to do as he pleased concerning one of the most fundamental tenets of democracy. WE WILL NEVER FORGET. — Owai King Ibe (@OwaiKingIbe) January 12, 2022  Short story on the ban of twitter in Nigeria Buhari gained nothing Buhari achieved nothing Buhari ruined a lot of businesses online C